    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Instead of the modulo operator, which has slightly different semantics, for non-negative integers, you can use the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se24/html/jls-15.html#jls-15.17.3\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><em>remainder</em> operator</a> <code>%</code>. For your exact example:</p>\n<pre><code>if ((a % 2) == 0)\n{\n    isEven = true;\n}\nelse\n{\n    isEven = false;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>This can be simplified to a one-liner:</p>\n<pre><code>isEven = (a % 2) == 0;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
